If you're new to it you'll probably want to find someone who's willing to work off of text description. Even then you'll want to use reference images. If it's a complicated scene you want, drawing it out to the best of your ability in mspaint helps a lot from what I've been told.

Have your references together before you contact an artist.

It's probably going to be more expensive than you realize.

Having an FA helps for contacting artists. Sadly, same thing with twitter. Be careful of the glut of russian and eastern european artists. I've never had a bad experience with them, but they tend to have english as a second language or pump it through google translate. They ask you to use simple sentences for a good reason.

Blokfort is open for comms a lot of the time and shows up in the thread now and again. He's really easy to work with so if you like his art I do recommend him.
